**HashMap internals and O(1) operations:**

```java
// HashMap: key → hash → bucket → linked list (or tree for >8 entries)
HashMap<String,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();  // default capacity 16, load 0.75
map.put("RELIANCE", 5000);    // O(1) avg: hash(key) % capacity → bucket
map.get("RELIANCE");          // O(1) avg
map.containsKey("TCS");       // O(1) avg — ALWAYS check before get!
map.getOrDefault("TCS", 0);  // O(1) — safe get with default
map.putIfAbsent("TCS", 100); // O(1) — put only if key missing
map.merge("TCS", 1, Integer::sum); // O(1) — merge: put or update
map.computeIfAbsent("TCS", k -> new ArrayList<>()).add("item");
// All O(1) average. O(n) worst case (all keys hash to same bucket).

// Iteration:
for (Map.Entry<String,Integer> e : map.entrySet())
    System.out.println(e.getKey() + "=" + e.getValue());
map.forEach((k,v) -> System.out.println(k+"="+v));
```
